text: Karakol (, Qaraqol/Karakol, formerly Przhevalsk (), is a city of about 68,800 people in Kyrgyzstan, near the eastern tip of Lake Issyk-Kul and about from the Kyrgyz-Chinese border. It is the capital of Issyk-Kul Region. Its area is and 66,294 people lived here in 2009. == References == == Other websites == * Category:Cities in Asia Category:Settlements in Kyrgyzstan
